#Text=Australian men , women win 2013 Asia-Oceania Wheelchair Basketball Championships
#Text=Sunday , December 1 , 2013
#Text=Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center , Bangkok —

#Text=The Australia men 's national wheelchair basketball team , known as the Rollers , and the Australia women 's national wheelchair basketball team , known as the Gliders , won gold medals on Friday , the final day of the Asia – Oceania Zone Wheelchair Basketball Championships in Bangkok , Thailand .
#Text=The eight day championship was opened on November 22 .
#Text=Asia – Oceania Zone Wheelchair Basketball Championships , Bangkok , 2013 .
#Text=IWBF President Maureen Orchard presents silver medals to the Chinese women 's team
#Text=Image : Hawkeye7 .
#Text=Australian Gliders are addressed by their head coach , Tom Kyle
#Text=Image : Hawkeye7 .
#Text=Maureen Orchard .
#Text=President and Secretary General of the International Wheelchair Basketball Federation
#Text=Image : Hawkeye7 .

#Text=Asia – Oceania Zone Wheelchair Basketball Championships — Australia 's Tristan Knowles
#Text=Image : Matthew Wells .

#Text=Ten countries competed for places at the International Wheelchair Basketball Federation ( IWBF ) World Championships next year — ten in the men 's : Japan , Iran , China , Malaysia , Taipei , Australia , Korea , Kuwait , New Zealand and Thailand ; and four in the women 's : Australia , Japan , China and Thailand .
#Text=For the Australians , it was a rare opportunity to play teams from neighboring countries .
#Text=Their efforts to help other teams were appreciated ; after one game the Kuwait men led a cheer of " Aussie ! Aussie ! Aussie ! "
#Text=To which the Thai women replied : " Oi ! Oi ! Oi ! "
#Text=Both the Australian teams went through the tournament undefeated .
#Text=The Gliders defeated China in the gold medal game 57 – 35 .
#Text=The Rollers then took to the court and defeated Korea 63 – 46 .
#Text=Iran and Japan won the men 's and women 's bronze medal matches .
#Text=This was one of four zone championships .
#Text=The zones correspond to those of the IPC and FIBA : Americas , Europe , Asia – Oceania and Africa .
#Text=Each zone is guaranteed one place at the World Championships .
#Text=Under recently-introduced rules , performance at the Paralympic games gains additional spots for the zone , not for the country .
#Text=Only the home team is guaranteed a place .

#Text=The new zone system has already proved controversial , with Algeria defeating South Africa in the recent Africa Zone Championships in Angola to grab the sole spot allocated to Africa , and Canada missing out on one of the four men 's spots for the Americas zone .
#Text=In a shock result , these places went to the United States , Argentina , Mexico and Colombia .
#Text=Great Britain , Turkey , Spain , Sweden , Italy , Germany and the Netherlands are to round out the championships as the men 's teams from the European Zone .
#Text=The men 's World Championship are to be held in July next year in Incheon , South Korea , while the women 's are to be in Toronto , Canada .
#Text=Maureen Orchard .
#Text=President and Secretary General of the IWBF told Wikinews the women 's competition will in no way be inferior to the men 's .
#Text=The women are to be put up in a five-star hotel , and play at Toronto 's Maple Leaf Gardens .
#Text=Without their men 's team competing , the women 's competition is expected to generate considerable interest in Canada .

#Text=The home team is to be joined by teams from the Netherlands , Germany , Great Britain , France , the United States , Brazil , Mexico , and Peru to compete against the winners from the Asia – Oceania Zone .
#Text=The sport of wheelchair basketball has great popularity .
#Text=In London , additional seats at the North Greenwich Arena sold out online within minutes .
